- Candidate 1 (Patchwork compilation): Key negative flags are inconsistent mastering and abrupt tonal/loudness jumps, occasional recessed lead vocals, and CD‑era over‑polish with sporadic AOR horn gloss. Those issues directly conflict with my desire for consistent, spacious production that preserves dynamics and keeps the lead intimate and upfront. Fragmented sequencing across multiple eras undermines song‑first, album‑oriented listening. The “AOR horn gloss” and over‑polish hint at occasional bombastic or arranged moments that could push the mix away from the restrained, vocal‑centric aesthetic I prefer.
